Title: Career Services at South Campus Welcome
Description: This event is to provide resources to students who live at South Campus, so they know what offices are available to them. We will be showcasing who Career Services is and what we can do!
Location: Ann and Alfred Goldstein Student Center, 201ABC, 401 Skytop Road, Syracuse, New York 13244, United States

Title: Scoop About Career Services
Description: Career Services & Let's Be Engaged (Student Events and Activities) would like you to join us at the Scoop About Career Services on the first floor of Schine. Stop by for help with resumes, job search tips, career questions, and more!
Location: Schine Student Center, Atrium , Syracuse, New York, United States

Title: DC/Boston  Immersion Info Session #1
Description: As part of the career development experience for our undergraduate students, we provide discovery immersive programs, where we bring students to designated geographic locations to engage and visit a handful of companies to learn about different industries, career paths, and life in that specific area. For this upcoming Spring Break 2026 (3.8.26-3.13.26), we will be visiting separately and simultaneously, Boston and Washington D.C. Join us for an information session to learn more about the immersion programs. We encourage Sophomores and Juniors to apply.
Location: Schine Student Center, 229, Syracuse, New York, United States

Title: Resume Blitz
Description: Join us for our Resume Blitz, a fast-paced event where career advisors provide on-the-spot resume reviews and tips. Bring your resume and get personalized feedback to help you stand out in your job search!
Location: Schine Student Center, 304ABC, Syracuse, New York, United States

Title: Boston Immersion 2026 - Selected Student Session
Description: This event is ONLY for students selected to participate in Central Career Services 2026 Boston Immersion Program. Meet fellow selected students and learn more about plans for the upcoming trip. Staff from career services will be showcasing the working schedule of what to anticipate. Please note that the schedule will continue to evolve leading up to the start of the program.
